(firstQuint)Effect of Wholegrain Wheat on Body Weight and Composition and Cardiovascular Risk.

 Objective: To study the effect of the 'wholegrain concept', i.

e.

 high intake of wheat wholegrain (WW) vs.

 refined wheat (RW) grain products on body weight and composition.

 Design: In this open-labeled randomized trial, 72 postmenopausal women with metabolic syndrome features were prescribed a mild calorie-restricted diet with a deficit of ~1,250kJ/d.

 Following 2 weeks run-in period on RW products, they were randomized to 12 weeks intervention with RW or WW products providing 2,000kJ/d.

